1 10–310.1.
2 (A) THE STATE BOARD SHALL ESTABLISH GUIDELINES FOR THE LOCAL
3 BOARDS TO IMPLEMENT A PROCESS TO ACCOMMODATE AND EXPEDITE VOTING FOR
4 ELDERLY VOTERS AND VOTERS WITH DISABILITIES, AS DEFINED IN THE FEDERAL
5 AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT, AT EACH EARLY VOTING CENTER AND
6 POLLING PLACE IN THE STATE.
7 (B) THE GUIDELINES ESTABLISHED BY THE STATE BOARD UNDER
8 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION SHALL INCLUDE:
9 (1) DEDICATED EXPEDITED LINES FOR ELDERLY VOTERS AND
10 VOTERS WITH DISABILITIES; AND
11 (2) CLEARLY MARKED SIGNAGE INDICATING THE AVAILABILITY OF
12 EXPEDITED SERVICES;
13 (3) PRIORITY SEATING FOR ELDERLY VOTERS AND VOTERS WITH
14 DISABILITIES IN WAITING AREAS; AND
15 (4) SPECIFIC PROVISIONS FOR HIGH–TRAFFIC EARLY VOTING
16 CENTERS AND POLLING PLACES.
17 (C) THE LOCAL BOARDS SHALL:
18 (1) IMPLEMENT THE GUIDELINES ESTABLISHED BY THE STATE
19 BOARD UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION; AND
20 (2) COLLECT FEEDBACK FROM ELDERLY VOTERS AND VOTERS WITH
21 DISABILITIES ON THE ACCOMMODATIONS AND EXPEDITED VOTING PROCESS WHILE
22 VOTING AT EARLY VOTING CENTERS AND POLLING PLACES IS IN PROGRESS AND
23 MAKE IMMEDIATE ADJUSTMENTS TO THE PROCESS AS NECESSARY.
24 (D) THE STATE BOARD SHALL MONITOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE
25 GUIDELINES ESTABLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION BY THE LOCAL
26 BOARDS AND SUBMIT A REPORT ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 15 EACH YEAR
27 IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING A STATEWIDE ELECTION TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY IN
28 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE THAT
29 INCLUDES:
30 (1) ANY CHALLENGES TO IMPLEMENTING THE GUIDELINES; AND

